.\" Manual page for Docker Commander. Keep the option list in sync with the
.\" flags in internal/config/config.go -- TestManPageDocumentsAllFlags enforces it.
.TH DOCKERCMD 1 "2026-06-15" "Docker Commander" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dockercmd \- monitor and control Docker from a single self-contained binary
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dockercmd
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B dockercmd
.IR action
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Docker Commander
is a single CGO-free binary with an embedded web UI that monitors and controls
Docker: containers, stacks, managed Compose projects, images, volumes, networks,
logs, events, alerts, multi-host, users/RBAC, an audit log, and an optional
remote MCP server for AI tools.
.PP
Run with no arguments it starts the server and serves the UI (default
.BR 127.0.0.1:8470 ).
The standalone actions below run a one-off task and exit instead of starting the
server.
.SH ACTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-version ", " version
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-make-certs " [host...]"
Write a self-signed TLS certificate and key into
.I <data-dir>/tls
for serving HTTPS, covering localhost plus any extra hostnames/IPs given. The
key is written mode 0600. For public hosts use a real CA / ACME instead.
.TP
.B \-\-self-upgrade " [" \fB\-\-check\fR ]
Download, verify (SHA-256) and atomically replace the binary with the latest
GitHub release. With
.B \-\-check
it only reports whether an update is available and exits.
.TP
.B \-\-install-service
Install Docker Commander as a background service: a hardened
.BR systemd (1)
unit on Linux (needs root), or a per-user
.BR launchd (8)
LaunchAgent on macOS. Also installs this man page.
.TP
.B \-\-uninstall-service
Stop and remove the service (the data dir and service user are left in place).
.TP
.B \-\-service-status
Show the service status.
.SH OPTIONS
Every option also has a
.B DC_*
environment variable and an identical config-file key; precedence is
command-line flag > environment variable > config file > default.
.TP
.BI \-config " path"
Path to a config file (KEY=VALUE, same keys as the environment).
.TP
.BI \-host " host"
Listen host/interface; use
.B 0.0.0.0
for all interfaces (default
.BR 127.0.0.1 ).
.TP
.BI \-port " n"
Listen port (default
.BR 8470 ).
.B \-p
is a shorthand for
.BR \-port .
.TP
.BI \-addr " host:port"
Full listen address (legacy; overrides
.B \-host
and
.BR \-port ).
.TP
.BI \-data-dir " dir"
Directory for the SQLite database and secrets.
.TP
.BI \-session-ttl " duration"
Session token lifetime (default
.BR 12h ).
.TP
.B \-dev
Enable development mode (permissive CORS).
.TP
.B \-update-check
Check GitHub for newer releases (default true; disable with
.BR DC_UPDATE_CHECK=0 ).
.TP
.B \-self-update
Allow an admin to apply an update from the web UI (default true; disable with
.BR DC_SELF_UPDATE=0 ).
.TP
.BI \-metrics-token " token"
Require this bearer token to scrape
.BR /metrics " (empty = open)."
.TP
.BI \-tls-cert " path"
PEM TLS certificate path (enables HTTPS together with
.BR \-tls-key ).
.TP
.BI \-tls-key " path"
PEM TLS private-key path.
.TP
.B \-mcp-enabled
Enable the remote MCP server + OAuth endpoints (off by default; requires HTTPS).
.TP
.BI \-mcp-public-url " url"
Externally reachable base URL (https://host[:port]) for the MCP OAuth flow.
.TP
.BI \-redis-addr " host:port"
Redis address for metric history (empty = in-memory ring buffer).
.TP
.BI \-redis-password " password"
Redis password.
.TP
.BI \-metrics-retention " duration"
How long to keep metric history (default
.BR 6h ).
.TP
.BI \-metrics-interval " duration"
How often to sample container stats; raise on hosts with many containers
(default
.BR 15s ).
.TP
.B \-pprof
Expose Go's net/http/pprof on a loopback-only listener
.RB ( 127.0.0.1:6060 )
for debugging.
.TP
.BI \-trusted-proxies " list"
Comma-separated reverse-proxy IPs/CIDRs whose
.B X-Forwarded-For
is trusted (empty = trust none; use the real peer).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The
.B DC_*
variables mirror the options above:
.BR DC_CONFIG ,
.BR DC_HOST ,
.BR DC_PORT ,
.BR DC_ADDR ,
.BR DC_DATA_DIR ,
.BR DC_DEV ,
.BR DC_UPDATE_CHECK ,
.BR DC_SELF_UPDATE ,
.BR DC_METRICS_TOKEN ,
.BR DC_TLS_CERT ,
.BR DC_TLS_KEY ,
.BR DC_MCP_ENABLED ,
.BR DC_MCP_PUBLIC_URL ,
.BR DC_REDIS_ADDR ,
.BR DC_REDIS_PASSWORD ,
.BR DC_REDIS_DB ,
.BR DC_METRICS_RETENTION ,
.BR DC_METRICS_INTERVAL ,
.BR DC_PPROF ,
.BR DC_TRUSTED_PROXIES .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/docker-commander/commander.conf
Default config file on Linux (override with
.B \-config
or
.BR DC_CONFIG ).
.TP
.I ~/.config/docker-commander/
Default data directory (database + secrets) for a foreground run.
.TP
.I /var/lib/dockercmd/
Data directory used by the installed systemd service.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start on all interfaces, port 9000:
.B dockercmd \-host 0.0.0.0 \-port 9000
.TP
Check for and install an update:
.B dockercmd \-\-self-upgrade \-\-check
.br
.B dockercmd \-\-self-upgrade
.TP
Install as a service (Linux):
.B sudo dockercmd \-\-install-service
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemd (1),
.BR launchd (8).
Full manual:
.UR https://github.com/koduj-dev/docker-commander
.UE
